Hi Wystan:  Thanks for your comment. Probaly the title &quot;preshtashka&quot; is a typo and it  should be &quot;prestashka&quot; as it appears in a similar Bain negative: <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/library_of_congress/2163469184/">www.flickr.com/photos/library_of_congress/2163469184/</a>

It is hard to find information about this word on the Web. A Christian Science Monitor article for Jan. 25, 1911 (subscription database) says of a London horse show: &quot;...the Russian section...will include competitions for a trotter and prestashka in wagon or droshky.  The animals in this class are driven together, but the horse on the near side trots, while the horse on the off side gallops.&quot;

We will fix the title.
